<scopecontent>
<p> The Commissioner's Correspondence also known as "Day Files" provides Commissioner Philip A. Shucet response to letters and e-mails (many transferred from the Governor's office) requesting assistance on topics involving transportation issues such as road construction, VDOT purchasing of property for right of way purposes and the impact of traffic congestion on the citizens of Virginia. Requests and questions of Secretary of Transportation Whittington Clement are among the correspondence transferred and handled by Commissioner Shucet's office.  Another feature of these records concerns the controversial proposed improvements to Interstate 81 offering much discussion concerning the impact on wildlife and the natural environment of the Shenandoah Valley. The records reflect citizen concerns about snow removal and or the lack of adequate cleaning of highways after snow storms are highlighted. The onslaught of traffic delays and subsequent delays due to road improvement construction are well documented in this collection. The inspection of bridges and budgetary discussions of ways to bring the cost down for the department are topics of interest.  
</p>
<p> This collection provides an index to all correspondence answered by the Commissioner's office. Some of the correspondence have attached reply letters sent out by the Commissioner's staff or Mr. Shucet. There is an index that provides the date, names, and topics of the various correspondence.  These records were microfilmed by the department before they were transferred to the library and each document has an assigned number displaying the order of filming. 
</p>
</scopecontent>
